control statements are used to handle the flow of execution.

java has provided few control statements

conditional control flow
=========================
if(condtion){

statements...

}



if(condition){
	statemnt
}
else{
 statemnt
} 



if(condition){
	statemnt
}
else if(condition){
	statement
}
else{
 statemnt
} 


if(condition){

  if(condition){
  
  }
}  


switch(expression){

	case value1: statement; break;
	case value2: etatement; break;
	..
	..
	case valueN: statement; break;
	default: statement;
}


break terminates the current flow of execution.
continue skips the current flow of execution.


LOOPS are used to execute similar code block multiple times.

for(inital condition; control condition; increment/decrement)
{
		statement...
		satement....
}

while(condition){  // if number of iteration not fixed 

}

do{  //if number of iteration not fixed and we must want to execute the statements atleast once.


}while(condition);

